<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="424" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,829,1360]" pageId="1" pageNumber="424">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,865,891]" pageId="1" pageNumber="424">Comments.</emphasis>
Based on the similarities of different parts of the copulatory organs, including the palpal tibia, cymbium and embolus in males, and the shape of receptacles in the weakly sclerotized epigyne in females, this genus was synonymized with 
<taxonomicName authority="Jocque &amp; Churchill, 2005" authorityName="Jocque &amp; Churchill" authorityYear="2005" box="[493,936,937,964]" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Tropizodium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="424" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[493,634,937,963]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="424">Tropizodium</emphasis>
Jocqué &amp; Churchill, 2005
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Dankittipakul, P. &amp; Jocque, R. &amp; Singtripop, T." box="[981,1287,937,964]" pageId="1" pageNumber="424" pagination="62 - 68" refId="ref6263" refString="Dankittipakul, P., Jocque, R. &amp; Singtripop, T. (2012) Two new species of the spider genus Tropizodium Jocque &amp; Churchill, 2005 with notes on the femoral organ clade from Southeast Asia (Araneae, Zodariidae, Zodariinae). Zootaxa, 3327 (1), 62 - 68. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3327.1.6" type="journal article" year="2012">
Dankittipakul 
<emphasis box="[1143,1194,937,963]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="424">et al</emphasis>
. (2012)
</bibRefCitation>
. Considering the unusual, disjunct generic distribution resulted from the noted synonymy (i.e. northwestern 
<collectingCountry box="[1244,1342,973,999]" name="Pakistan" pageId="1" pageNumber="424">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[1355,1436,973,999]" country="China" name="Hainan" pageId="1" pageNumber="424">Hainan</collectingRegion>
[southernmost 
<collectingCountry box="[319,391,1009,1036]" name="China" pageId="1" pageNumber="424">China</collectingCountry>
], south to 
<collectingCountry box="[507,610,1009,1035]" name="Australia" pageId="1" pageNumber="424">Australia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[666,863,1009,1035]" name="French Polynesia" pageId="1" pageNumber="424">French Polynesia</collectingCountry>
, Hawaii), and the diverse morphology of the palps in species considered in the genus, we do not consider this taxonomic act justified.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,829,1360]" pageId="1" pageNumber="424">
<taxonomicName authority="Jocque &amp; Churchill, 2005" authorityName="Jocque &amp; Churchill" authorityYear="2005" box="[199,782,1081,1108]" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Tropizodium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="424" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peregrinum">
<emphasis box="[199,479,1081,1107]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="424">Tropizodium peregrinum</emphasis>
Jocqué &amp; Churchill, 2005
</taxonomicName>
(the generotype described from 
<collectingCountry box="[1154,1259,1081,1108]" name="Australia" pageId="1" pageNumber="424">Australia</collectingCountry>
) differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ovtchinnikov" authorityYear="2006" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Indozodion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="424" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inayatullahi">
<emphasis box="[1420,1429,1082,1107]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="424">I</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[151,286,1117,1143]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="424">inayatullahi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the following characters (those of the latter noted in parentheses): 1) embolus short, almost straight, originating at a 10 o’clock position (
<emphasis box="[553,583,1154,1179]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="424">vs.</emphasis>
long embolus, originating at about 7 o’clock position and making a course of about 180º), and 2) the lack of conductor (
<emphasis box="[616,639,1190,1215]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="424">vs</emphasis>
. present). Therefore, we hereby remove 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ovtchinnikov" authorityYear="2006" box="[1088,1214,1189,1215]" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Indozodion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="424" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1088,1214,1189,1215]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="424">Indozodion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the synonymy of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jocque &amp; Churchill" authorityYear="2005" box="[179,320,1225,1251]" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Tropizodium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="424" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[179,320,1225,1251]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="424">Tropizodium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It is noteworthy that the 
<typeStatus box="[596,644,1226,1252]" pageId="1" pageNumber="424">type</typeStatus>
material of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ovtchinnikov" authorityYear="2006" box="[774,931,1225,1252]" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Indozodion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="424" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inayatullahi">
<emphasis box="[774,783,1226,1251]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="424">I</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[796,931,1225,1251]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="424">inayatullahi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were not located in ZMMU (K. G. Mikhailov, pers. comm.), where they are supposed to be deposited according to 
<bibRefCitation author="Ovtchinnikov, S. V." box="[918,1157,1261,1288]" pageId="1" pageNumber="424" pagination="77 - 79" refId="ref6606" refString="Ovtchinnikov, S. V. (2006) New genus and species of spiders of the subfamily Zodariinae (Araneae, Zodariidae) from Pakistan. Vestnik Zoologii, 40, 77 - 79." type="journal article" year="2006">Ovtchinnikov (2006)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,829,1360]" box="[199,1386,1297,1324]" pageId="1" pageNumber="424">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,359,1297,1323]" pageId="1" pageNumber="424">Composition.</emphasis>
Two species: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ovtchinnikov" authorityYear="2006" box="[518,786,1297,1323]" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Indozodion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="424" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inayatullahi">
<emphasis box="[518,786,1297,1323]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="424">Indozodion inayatullahi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[793,916,1297,1323]" pageId="1" pageNumber="424">comb. rev.</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Roewer, 1960)" authorityName="Zamani &amp; Marusik" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Roewer" baseAuthorityYear="1960" box="[971,1277,1297,1324]" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Indozodion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="424" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lindbergi" status="comb. n.">
<emphasis box="[971,980,1298,1323]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="424">I</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[994,1096,1297,1323]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="424">lindbergi</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Roewer, C. F." box="[1110,1269,1297,1324]" pageId="1" pageNumber="424" pagination="1 - 53" refId="ref6705" refString="Roewer, C. F. (1960) Solifugen und Opilioniden - Araneae Orthognathae, Haplogynae und Entelegynae (Contribution a l'etude de la faune d'Afghanistan 23). Goteborgs Kungliga Vetenskaps och Vitterhets Samhalles Handlingar, Series 6, B 8 (7), 1 - 53." type="journal article" year="1960">Roewer, 1960</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1284,1386,1297,1323]" pageId="1" pageNumber="424">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1284,1386,1297,1323]" pageId="1" pageNumber="424" rank="species">comb. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1028,1333,1360]" pageId="1" pageNumber="424" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,829,1360]" box="[199,1028,1333,1360]" pageId="1" pageNumber="424">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,1333,1359]" pageId="1" pageNumber="424">Distribution.</emphasis>
Northwestern to northern 
<collectingCountry box="[649,744,1333,1359]" name="Pakistan" pageId="1" pageNumber="424">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
and eastern 
<collectingCountry box="[884,1025,1333,1359]" name="Afghanistan" pageId="1" pageNumber="424">Afghanistan</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
